posts.name: Elliot Scher
posts.cooked:
I’ve been able to use pathweaver perfectly fine up until now. Now I get this error:

pathweaver error 777×700 216 KB

pathweaver error 777×700 216 KB

pathweaver error 777×700 216 KB

I have no idea what this means. Does anyone know how to fix it? Thanks!!

posts.name: Elliot Scher
posts.cooked: The start tool option in VS code

posts.name: Sameer C
posts.cooked: Try running “Wpilib: Install Tools” while connected to a wifi network and see if pathweaver has any updates.

posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked: Have you added custom games? * Loads a game from a directory. If there are multiple JSON files in the directory, one of them must be named * "game.json". If not, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. If only one JSON file is in the directory, * it may have any name (but must still end with ".json").

posts.name: Elliot Scher
posts.cooked: No I haven’t. I tried completely uninstalling and reinstalling wpilib but to no avail

posts.name: Elliot Scher
posts.cooked: updating to the new wpilib 2023.3.1 resolved the issue
